Bui far more notieeable than his affection for certain words is Sallusi’s striving after variety (Quin- tilian 10. 3. 8 manifestus autetiam eu opere ipso labor). He may be regarded as the leader in the revolt against Ciceronian concinnity‚ the correspondence and balance of phrase and construction—a movemeni which Livy and Tacitus developed still further.
